      "name": "Cross-study hemolysis model synthesis — literature corpus 2010–2023",
      "description": "A synthesis of multiple prior studies examining power-law hemolysis model coefficients across centrifugal and axial blood pump geometries. The synthesis aggregates data from 14 published validation campaigns and derives consolidated coefficient uncertainty bounds used as prior distributions in the Monte Carlo UQ step. The narrative richness of this node — spanning device classes, flow regimes, and hemolysis measurement protocols — provides strong contextual grounding for the MRL 5 assessment. Its role as an integrative evidence node is understood by the assessment team to confer foundational status, consolidating upstream experimental campaigns into a single coherent prior.",
